txt.en: 'What is that thing?!'
'Looks like a door.'
A sharp pain enters your head as the watching stone shows visions of the past.
'What do we do?'
Instance: Borangos The Horror
As Borangos and Urudanî leave, you are relieved to have not been noticed.
'Well I did not build it!'
'Or a seal on some sort of chamber.'
'The incident at Naerband. Do I have your assurance the Uruk will not step out of line again?'
'We should tell Urudanî. She will want to know about this.'
'Good, Thraknûl is an unknowing ally. Let him work for us until he is no longer of use.'
'Continue to bind him around your flame, Urudanî.'
'Dúrossul has informed me of the recent intruder in Nargroth.'
'I do not believe it is worth pursuing one [placeholder], at this moment.'
'Now Urudanî, we must be patient. The time is coming.'
'I have been waiting for this moment ever since you freed me from my prison.'
'Not the mountain that stands on the plain of Gorgoroth, but what lies beneath it.'
'While all those in Mordor seek land, riches, and power, I seek something greater.'
'What gives our realm its strength, and drives me?'
'Orodruin.'
'You will find out this in due time, my most devoted.'
'Come, we have much more to accomplish.'
